### Location CRUD API Tests
### Base URL: https://localhost:7001/api

### 1. Get All Locations
GET {{baseUrl}}/Location
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

### 2. Get All Locations (including inactive)
GET {{baseUrl}}/Location?includeInactive=true
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

### 3. Get Location by ID
GET {{baseUrl}}/Location/{{locationId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

### 4. Create New Location
POST {{baseUrl}}/Location
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Central Warehouse",
  "type": 0,
  "address": "123 Main St, City, State 12345",
  "manager": "John Smith"
}

### 5. Create Sub-Location
POST {{baseUrl}}/Location
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "North Depot",
  "type": 1,
  "address": "456 North Ave, City, State 12345",
  "manager": "Jane Doe",
  "parentLocationId": "{{parentLocationId}}"
}

### 6. Create Vehicle Location
POST {{baseUrl}}/Location
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Truck #001",
  "type": 3,
  "address": "Mobile Unit",
  "manager": "Bob Johnson",
  "parentLocationId": "{{parentLocationId}}"
}

### 7. Update Location
PUT {{baseUrl}}/Location/{{locationId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "id": "{{locationId}}",
  "name": "Updated Central Warehouse",
  "type": 0,
  "address": "123 Updated Main St, City, State 12345",
  "manager": "John Smith Updated",
  "parentLocationId": null,
  "isActive": true
}

### 8. Deactivate Location (Soft Delete)
PUT {{baseUrl}}/Location/{{locationId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "id": "{{locationId}}",
  "name": "Central Warehouse",
  "type": 0,
  "address": "123 Main St, City, State 12345",
  "manager": "John Smith",
  "parentLocationId": null,
  "isActive": false
}

### 9. Delete Location (Soft Delete)
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/Location/{{locationId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

### Location Types Reference:
### 0 = Warehouse
### 1 = Office  
### 2 = Field
### 3 = Vehicle
### 4 = Customer Site
### 5 = Supplier
### 6 = Other

